  "notes": "nói = “to say” or “to speak.” It’s the basic verb for expressing something in words.\n\nUse it for both short statements and general speaking. You usually put the content right after nói, or add với + person to show who you’re speaking to.\n\nVery common combos: nói chuyện (chat), nói tiếng + language (speak a language), nói dối (lie).  \nClose synonym: bảo (tell) — more like giving information or instructions to someone specific.",
